title: BBC Radio 1 Big Weekend 2018 Vol 4 [Video Album]
description:
MPEG2 720HD 320kbps @ 48 KZ

BBC Radio 1 Biggest Weekend is a 4 Day festival of Live Music held over the May Bank Holiday weekend to replace Glastonbury which is also broadcast by the British Broadcasting Corporation, one of the oldest broadcasters in the World.

Not dependent on the fiscal income of Sponsors or Donors the BBC is funded by a TV license which the entire population of the UK who own a TV set must pay, giving the BBC a set and predictable income and a huge advantage for that reason.

Enjoy some of the best video and live sound quality you are ever likely to see from any TV broadcaster in the World today.   

If you ever wondered why such a tiny group of Island made up of Scotland, Northern Ireland, Wales and England can put out so much original music, in part you can thank BBC Music from 1967 and before that the 1960s Offshore Pirate Radio Station which ringed the Islands.
